<setup>
  <select assignNames="(a)">
    <option>
      <number>27</number>
    </option>
    <option>
      <number>432</number>
    </option>
  </select>
  <function symbolic formula="ln(x^4+$a)" name="f" />
  <math name="c" simplify>
    $$f(0)
  </math>
  <math name="d" simplify>
    (3*$a)^(1/4)
  </math>

  <math name="ans1" format="latex">
    (0,\infty)
  </math>
  <math name="ans2" format="latex">
    (-\infty,0)
  </math>
  <math name="ans3">
    none
  </math>
  <math name="ans4">
    (0,$c)
  </math>
  <math name="ans5" format="latex">
    (-$d,$d)
  </math>
  <math name="ans6" format="latex">
    (-\infty,-$d)\cup ($d,\infty)
  </math>
</setup>

<p>
  Let <m>f(x)=$f</m>.
  Answer the following questions.
</p>

<p>
  1. Find the largest <em>open</em> interval(s) on which
  <m>f</m> is increasing. If there is more than one interval,
  write your answer as a union of the intervals.
</p>
<p>
  Answer (in interval notation):
  <answer><award>$ans1</award></answer>
</p>

<p>
  2. Find the largest <em>open</em> interval(s) on which
  <m>f</m> is decreasing. If there is more than one interval,
  write your answer as a union of the intervals.
</p>
<p>
  Answer (in interval notation):
  <answer><award>$ans2</award></answer>
</p>

<p>
  3. Find the local maxima of <m>f</m>.
  <alert>List your answers as points in the form</alert>
  <m>(a,b)</m>.
</p>
<p>
  Answer (separate by commas):
  <answer><award symbolicEquality>$ans3</award></answer>
</p>

<p>
  4. Find the local minima of <m>f</m>.
  <alert>List your answers as points in the form</alert>
  <m>(a,b)</m>.
</p>
<p>
  Answer (separate by commas):
  <answer><award>$ans4</award></answer>
</p>

<p>
  5. Find the largest <em>open</em> interval(s) on
  which <m>f</m> is concave upward. If there is
  more than one interval, write your answer as a
  union of the intervals.
</p>
<p>
  Answer (in interval notation):
  <answer><award>$ans5</award></answer>
</p>

<p>
  6. Find the largest <em>open</em> interval(s) on
  which <m>f</m> is concave downward. If there is
  more than one interval, write your answer as a
  union of the intervals.
</p>
<p>
  Answer (in interval notation):
  <answer><award>$ans6</award></answer>
</p>

